==English==

===Etymology===
Originating from a speech by US politician William Jennings Bryan in 1896, describing a [[metaphor]]ical [[crucifixion]] of the [[working class]] by maintaining the [[gold standard]]. It has since acquired a more generic meaning.

===Phrase===
'''[[cross]] [[of]] [[gold]]'''

# A public policy which puts the interests of the [[rich]] ahead of those of the [[poor]].

